21/12/2008
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- Lawyer Loucas Louca was named as the country's new justice minister on Friday (December 19th), replacing Kypros Chrysostomides, who resigned after a dangerous prisoner escaped during treatment at a hospital. 
Louca, 52, is a personal friend of President Demetris Christofias. 
He assumes the post on Monday.
In other news, Christofias announced on Saturday that he is resigning as leader of his left-wing party Communist Party (AKEL). 
He says he wants to devote more time to the ongoing reunification talks. 
(Xinhua, RIA Novosti - 20/12/08; MIA, Cyprus Mail, Financial Mirror - 19/12/08)
